Scenario-Based Questions:
13. You receive an alert that a core network switch is down—what are your immediate steps?
	• Check monitoring tools for additional alerts.
	• Attempt to ping the switch and check for connectivity.
	• Review switch logs to identify errors or hardware failures.
	• If the issue persists, escalate to the network engineering team while documenting the impact and any troubleshooting steps taken.
14. A critical system patch needs to be applied, but it could impact network availability. How would you proceed?
	• Coordinate with stakeholders to schedule a maintenance window.
	• Test the patch in a staging environment first.
	• Implement a rollback plan in case issues arise.
	• Apply the patch and monitor system performance post-installation.
15. An end-user reports slow network performance—how do you diagnose and resolve the issue?
	• Check network monitoring tools for bandwidth spikes.
	• Run ping and traceroute to detect latency.
	• Check firewall rules for traffic blocks.
	• Analyze Splunk logs for potential issues.
	• Engage the network team if hardware-related issues are suspected.

